eya_def_tools.data_models.result.Result
Collection of results a quantity along specific dimensions.
Attributes: label (Optional[str]): Label of the results. Default is None. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the result. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the result. Default is None. assessment_period (Optional[AssessmentPeriod(StrEnum)]): Period of or in time that has been assessed and for which the results are applicable. Default is None. dimensions (Optional[list[ResultsDimension(StrEnum)]]): Dimensions along which the results are binned (all result values in the same results object must have the same dimensions). Default is None. statistics (list[ResultStatistic]): List of result statistic objects that each include result values for a specific statistic type.

eya_def_tools.data_models.result.ResultStatistic
Result values for one specific statistic type.
Attributes: description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the result statistic. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the result statistic. Default is None. statistic_type (StatisticType(StrEnum)): Type of statistic in the results component. values (UnionType[float, list[tuple[list[UnionType[float, int, str]], float]]]): Result as a single number or values at coordinates.

eya_def_tools.data_models.eya_def.EyaDefDocument
IEC 61400-15-2 EYA DEF top-level data model.
Attributes: uri (Optional[Url]): URI of the EYA DEF JSON document, which should have the field name '$id' in the JSON document. Default is None. schema_uri (Url): URI of the EYA DEF JSON Schema, which should have the field name '$schema' in the JSON document. It is assumed to be the latest published version if not included. Default is https://raw.githubusercontent.com/IEC-61400-15/eya_def/blob/main/iec_61400-15-2_eya_def.schema.json. uuid (Optional[UUID]): UUID of the EYA DEF JSON document. Default is None. title (str): Title of the energy yield assessment (EYA) report. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the energy yield assessment (EYA) report. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the energy yield assessment (EYA) report. Default is None. project_name (str): Name of the project under assessment. project_country (Alpha2CountryCode(StrEnum)): The ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 two-letter code of the country where the project under assessment is located. document_id (Optional[str]): The ID of the report document; not including the version when 'document_version' is used. This will typically follow the convention of the document management system of the issuing organisation(s). Default is None. document_version (Optional[str]): Version of the report document, also known as revision. As with the 'document_id', this will typically follow the document versioning convention of the document management system of the issuing organisation(s). Default is None. issue_date (date): Report issue date in the ISO 8601 standard format for a calendar date, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD. contributors (list[ReportContributor]): List of report contributors (e.g. author and verifier) issuing_organisations (list[Organisation]): The organisation(s) issuing the report (e.g. consultant). receiving_organisations (Optional[list[Organisation]]): The organisation(s) receiving the report (e.g. client), if relevant. Default is None. contract_reference (Optional[str]): Reference to contract between the issuing and receiving organisations that governs the energy yield assessment (EYA) report document, if relevant. Default is None. confidentiality_classification (Optional[str]): Confidentiality classification of the report document, if relevant. Default is None. epsg_srid (int): EPSG Spatial Reference System Identifier (SRID) for the Coordinate Reference System (CRS) used for all spatial data (e.g. turbine locations) in the EYA DEF JSON document. All location coordinates must be reported in the same CRS, which must be one that has an EPSG code. If different CRSs are used the data must be converted to be consistent with the EPSG code specified here. wind_farms (list[WindFarmConfiguration]): List of all wind farms considered in the EYA. This should comprise internal, external and future wind farms, including those used as reference wind farms in the wind resource assessment, if any. If different configurations are assessed for one or more internal and/or future wind farms in different scenarios, a wind farm object must be completed for each unique configuration, with the relevant configurations for each scenario referenced by wind farm ID. measurement_stations (Annotated[Optional[list[dict[str, Any]]], IEATask43WraDataModel]): List of measurement station metadata documents according to the IEA Wind Task 43 WRA Data Model, including all measurement stations relevant to the EYA, if any. It is recommended that one metadata document be completed for each measurement station, although the WRA Data Model allows for grouping multiple measurement stations into a single document. Default is None. reference_wind_farms (Optional[list[ReferenceWindFarm]]): List of metadata documents for the reference operational wind farms relevant to the EYA, if any. One metadata document shall be completed for each relevant reference operational wind farm. Default is None. reference_meteorological_datasets (Optional[list[ReferenceMeteorologicalDataset]]): List of metadata documents for reference meteorological datasets used in the long-term prediction process of the EYA, which may include details of for example ground-based meteorological stations, reanalysis datasets and mesoscale model datasets used as long-termreferences. Default is None. wind_resource_assessments (list[WindResourceAssessment]): List of wind resource assessments, including results, at the measurement station locations. turbine_models (Annotated[Optional[list[dict[str, Any]]], IEC61400x16PowerCurveDataModel]): List of wind turbine model specifications. Default is None. scenarios (Optional[list[Scenario]]): List of energy yield assessment scenarios. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.general_metadata.Organisation
Issuing or receiving organisation of an energy yield assessment.
Attributes: name (str): Entity name of the organisation. abbreviation (Optional[str]): Abbreviated name of the organisation. Default is None. address (Optional[str]): Address of the organisation. Default is None. contact_name (Optional[str]): Name(s) of contact person(s) in the organisation. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.general_metadata.ReportContributor
Contributor to an energy yield assessment.
Attributes: name (str): Name of the contributor. email_address (Optional[EmailStr]): Email address of the contributor. Default is None. contributor_type (ReportContributorType(StrEnum)): Type of contributor. contribution_comments (Optional[str]): Comments to clarify contribution. Default is None. completion_date (Optional[date]): Contribution completion date (format YYYY-MM-DD). Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.reference_met_data.ReferenceMeteorologicalDataset
Metadata for a reference meteorological dataset.
The schema describes a dataset at a single horizontal spatial location. Separate data model instances need to be used to describe data at different location from the same source dataset (e.g. different grid cells from a reanalysis dataset).
Attributes: id (str): Unique ID for the reference meteorological dataset within the EYA DEF document. description (str): Description of the meteorological dataset. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the meteorological dataset. Default is None. location (Location): The horizontal spatial location of the meteorological data.

eya_def_tools.data_models.reference_wind_farm.ReferenceWindFarm
Reference wind farm.
Attributes: id (str): Unique ID for the reference wind farm within the EYA DEF document. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the reference wind farm. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the reference wind farm. Default is None. wind_farm_id (str): The ID of the wind farm in the 'wind_farms' section of the top-level of the EYA DEF document, containing the configuration data for the reference wind farm. datasets (list[ReferenceWindFarmDataset]): List of metadata documents describing the operational datasets from the reference wind farm that were used in the EYA.

eya_def_tools.data_models.scenario.Scenario
Single unique energy yield assessment scenario.
Attributes: id (Optional[str]): Optional unique identifier of the scenario. Default is None. label (str): Label of the scenario. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the scenario. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the scenario. Default is None. is_main_scenario (Optional[bool]): Whether or not this is the main scenario in the report. Default is None. operational_lifetime_length_years (float): Number of years of project operational lifetime. wind_farm_ids (list[str]): List of the IDs for all wind farms included in the scenario. Each ID refers to a wind farm configuration data object within the 'wind_farms' section of the top-level of the EYA DEF document. Only wind farms for which turbine interaction effects are modelled shall be included. turbine_wind_resource_assessment (TurbineWindResourceAssessment): Wind resource assessment at the turbine locations. energy_assessment (EnergyAssessment): Energy assessment details and results, including gross energy, plant performance, net energy and uncertainties.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_farm.WindFarmConfiguration
A collection of wind turbines considered as one unit (plant).
Attributes: id (str): Unique identifier of the wind farm. label (str): Label or name of the wind farm. abbreviation (Optional[str]): Optional abbreviated label of the wind farm. Default is None. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the wind farm. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the wind farm. Default is None. turbines (list[TurbineConfiguration]): List of specifications for constituent turbines. relevance (WindFarmRelevance(StrEnum)): The relevance of the wind farm for the assessment ('internal', 'external' or 'future'). operational_lifetime_start_date (date): Operational lifetime start date of the wind farm (format YYYY-MM-DD). operational_lifetime_end_date (Optional[date]): Operational lifetime end date of the wind farm (format YYYY-MM-DD). Default is None. installed_capacity (float): The maximum production (in MW) of the wind farm under typical conditions. If there are features in place to increase power output beyond the stated nameplate power of the turbines (e.g. so-called power boost solutions), the wind farm installed capacity should correspond to that increased power, insofar as it is reached under typical conditions and not only in rare exceptions. export_capacity (Optional[float]): The maximum permanently transmittable power (in MW) from the wind farm at the grid connection, or equivalent. Default is None. restrictions (Optional[list[OperationalRestriction]]): List of operational restrictions at the wind farm level. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_resource.WindResourceAssessment
Wind resource assessment at the measurement location(s).
Attributes: wind_resource_assessment_id (str): Unique ID of the wind resource assessment within the EYA DEF document. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the wind resource assessment. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the wind resource assessment. Default is None. results (WindResourceResults): Results of the wind resource assessment at the measurement location(s).

eya_def_tools.data_models.spatial.Location
Specification of a horizontal location in space.
Attributes: x (float): Location x-coordinate (typically easing). y (float): Location y-coordinate (typically northing).

eya_def_tools.data_models.reference_wind_farm.ReferenceWindFarmDataset
Reference wind farm operational dataset.
Attributes: label (Optional[str]): Label of the reference wind farm dataset. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the dataset. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the dataset. Default is None. data_supplier_organisation (Organisation): The organisation that supplied the data. data_type (OperationalDataType(StrEnum)): The type of data in the operational data, categorised as 'scada' for data from a Supervisory Control and Data Acquisition (SCADA) system, 'metered' for data from a production meter, 'environmental_measurement' for data from an (on-site) environmental measurement station such as a meteorological mast or a remote sensing device (RSD) and 'other' for any other type of unit. data_source_type (DataSourceType(StrEnum)): The type of the operational data source. Primary data, such as primary SCADA data, comes directly from the source without processing. Report data refers to data extracted from report document, such as monthly operational reports. Other secondary data comprises all other data source categories, such as secondary SCADA data provided in processed (harmonised) form by a data management service provider. used_data_variables (list[ReferenceWindFarmDataVariable]): A list of the types of data variables included in this dataset and used in the assessment. For a large dataset (such as a full wind turbine SCADA dataset) this field should not include all the variables but only the ones that were used in the analysis. time_resolution (TimeResolution(StrEnum)): Time resolution of the data. data_period_start_date (date): Start of the data period in the ISO 8601 standard format for a calendar date, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD. data_period_end_date (date): End of the data period in the ISO 8601 standard format for a calendar date, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_resource.TurbineWindResourceAssessment
Wind resource assessment at the turbine locations.
Attributes: wind_resource_assessment_id_reference (str): The ID of the wind resource assessment on which the turbine wind resource assessment is based. This must refer to an ID of a wind resource assessment included at the top level of the EYA DEF. The schema requires that a turbine wind resource assessment is based on only one wind resource assessment. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the turbine wind resource assessment. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the turbine wind resource assessment. Default is None. wind_spatial_modelling_processes (list[AssessmentProcessDescription]): Wind spatial modelling processes used in the assessment. results (TurbineWindResourceResults): Results of the wind resource assessment at the turbine location(s). wind_uncertainty_assessment (WindUncertaintyAssessment): Wind related uncertainty assessment categories including results.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_farm.OperationalRestriction
Specifications of a restriction that limits power output.
In the current draft of the schema, 'label', 'description' and 'comments' fields are available to describe the restriction with free text. This is intended to be expanded into a more comprehensive data model.
Attributes: label (str): Short label to indicate the type of operational restriction. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the operational restriction. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the operational restriction. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_farm.TurbineConfiguration
Specification of all details for a turbine configuration.
Attributes: id (str): Unique identifier of the turbine. label (Optional[str]): Label of the turbine, if different from the 'id'. Default is None. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the turbine. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the turbine. Default is None. location (Location): The horizontal spatial location of the turbine. ground_level_altitude (float): The ground level altitude (base elevation) of the turbine (in m). hub_height (float): The hub height of the turbine (in m). turbine_model_id (str): Unique identifier of the turbine model. operational_lifetime_start_date (Optional[date]): Operational lifetime start date of the individual turbine (format YYYY-MM-DD). Default is None. operational_lifetime_end_date (Optional[date]): Operational lifetime end date of the individual turbine (format YYYY-MM-DD). Default is None. restrictions (Optional[list[OperationalRestriction]]): List of operational restrictions at the turbine level. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_resource.WindResourceResults
Wind resource assessment results at measurement locations.
Attributes: wind_speed (list[Result]): Final long-term wind speed estimates at the measurement location(s)in metre per second. probability (Optional[list[Result]]): Final long-term probability distribution estimates at the measurement location(s), such as wind speed probability distributions or joint wind speed and direction frequency distributions, as dimensionless values. Default is None. turbulence_intensity (Optional[list[Result]]): Final long-term turbulence intensity estimates at the measurement location(s) as dimensionless values. Default is None. wind_shear_exponent (Optional[list[Result]]): Final long-term power law wind shear exponent estimates at the measurement location(s). Default is None. temperature (Optional[list[Result]]): Final long-term temperature estimates at the measurement location(s) in degree C. Default is None. air_density (Optional[list[Result]]): Final long-term air density estimates at the measurement location(s) in kilogram per cubic metre. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.plant_performance.PlantPerformanceSubcategory
Plant performance loss assessment subcategory.
Attributes: label (PlantPerformanceSubcategoryLabel(StrEnum)): Label of the plant performance loss subcategory. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the plant performance loss subcategory. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the plant performance loss subcategory. Default is None. basis (AssessmentBasis(StrEnum)): Basis of plant performance loss subcategory assessment. The basis describes the level of detail of the calculation or estimate used in the assessment of the subcategory. variability (TimeVariabilityType(StrEnum)): Considered variability in the plant performance loss subcategory. assessment_process_descriptions (Optional[list[AssessmentProcessDescription]]): Description of calculation processes used in the assessment of the plant performance loss subcategory. Default is None. elements (Optional[list[PlantPerformanceSubcategoryElement]]): Plant performance loss assessment elements that fall under the subcategory. The element objects include details and results at the element level. A breakdown of plant performance loss subcategories into elements is optional and can be included only for a subset of the subcategories, as relevant. Whereas the categories and subcategories are fixed, the user may freely define element labels. Default is None. results (PlantPerformanceResults): Plant performance assessment subcategory results.

eya_def_tools.data_models.plant_performance.PlantPerformanceSubcategoryElement
Plant performance loss assessment subcategory element.
Attributes: label (str): Label of the plant performance loss subcategory element. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the plant performance loss subcategory element. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the plant performance loss subcategory element. Default is None. basis (AssessmentBasis(StrEnum)): Basis of plant performance loss subcategory element assessment. The basis describes the level of detail of the calculation or estimate used in the assessment of the element. variability (TimeVariabilityType(StrEnum)): Considered variability in the plant performance loss subcategory element. is_independent (bool): Whether the plant performance loss subcategory element is independent of all other elements. Default is True. assessment_process_descriptions (Optional[list[AssessmentProcessDescription]]): Description of calculation processes used in the assessment of the plant performance loss subcategory element. Default is None. results (PlantPerformanceResults): Plant performance assessment subcategory element results.

eya_def_tools.data_models.reference_wind_farm.ReferenceWindFarmDataVariable
Reference wind farm operational data variable.
Attributes: label (str): Label of the data variable. This is currently free text but should be replaced by a list of enum options. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the data variable. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the data variable. Default is None. data_level (OperationalDataLevel(StrEnum)): Whether the operational data variable is provided for each individual wind turbine ('turbine_level'), is aggregated at the wind farm level ('wind_farm_level') or corresponds to a different ('other') unit such as an environmental measurement station. statistic_types (list[StatisticType(StrEnum)]): A list of the types of statistics included for this data variable. measurement_point (Optional[str]): Optional clarification of the point of measurement, such as the location of the energy meter for metered production. Default is None. raw_data_recovery_rate (Optional[list[Result]]): Dimensionless raw data recovery rate for the variable. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_resource.TurbineWindResourceResults
Wind resource assessment results at turbine locations.
Attributes: wind_speed (list[Result]): Final long-term wind speed estimates at the turbine location(s) in metre per second. probability (Optional[list[Result]]): Final long-term probability distribution estimates at the turbine location(s), such as wind speed probability distributions or joint wind speed and direction frequency distributions, as dimensionless values. Default is None. turbulence_intensity (Optional[list[Result]]): Final long-term turbulence intensity estimates at the turbine location(s) as dimensionless values. Default is None. wind_shear_exponent (Optional[list[Result]]): Final long-term power law wind shear exponent estimates at the turbine location(s). Default is None. temperature (Optional[list[Result]]): Final long-term temperature estimates at the turbine location(s) in degree C. Default is None. air_density (Optional[list[Result]]): Final long-term air density estimates at the turbine location(s) in kilogram per cubic metre. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_uncertainty.WindUncertaintyAssessment
Wind related uncertainty assessment broken into categories.
Attributes: categories (list[WindUncertaintyCategory]): Wind related uncertainty assessment categories including results. results (UncertaintyResults): Overall wind related uncertainty assessment results.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_uncertainty.UncertaintyResults
Uncertainty assessment results.
Attributes: relative_wind_speed_uncertainty (Optional[list[Result]]): Uncertainty assessment results as dimensionless relative values expressed in terms of wind speed and calculated as the standard deviation of the wind speed uncertainty distribution divided by the mean wind speed. Default is None. relative_energy_uncertainty (Optional[list[Result]]): Uncertainty assessment results as dimensionless relative values expressed in terms of AEP (annual energy production) and calculated as the standard deviation of the energy uncertainty distribution divided by the net P50 (50% probability of exceedance level) AEP. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_uncertainty.WindUncertaintyCategory
Category of a wind related uncertainty assessment.
Attributes: label (WindUncertaintyCategoryLabel(StrEnum)): Label of the wind related uncertainty assessment category. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the wind related uncertainty category. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the wind related uncertainty category. Default is None. subcategories (list[WindUncertaintySubcategory]): Wind related uncertainty assessment subcategories that fall under the category. The subcategory objects include details and results at the subcategory level. results (UncertaintyResults): Wind related uncertainty assessment category results.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_uncertainty.WindUncertaintySubcategory
Subcategory of a wind related uncertainty assessment.
Attributes: label (WindUncertaintySubcategoryLabel(StrEnum)): Label of the wind related uncertainty subcategory. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the wind related uncertainty subcategory. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the wind related uncertainty subcategory. Default is None. elements (Optional[list[WindUncertaintySubcategoryElement]]): Wind related uncertainty assessment elements that fall under the subcategory. The element objects include details and results at the element level. A breakdown of wind related uncertainty subcategories into elements is optional and can be included only for a subset of the subcategories, as relevant. Whereas the categories and subcategories are fixed, the user may freely define element labels. Default is None. results (UncertaintyResults): Wind related uncertainty assessment subcategory results.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_uncertainty.WindUncertaintySubcategoryElement
Subcategory element of a wind related uncertainty assessment.
Attributes: label (str): Label of the wind related uncertainty subcategory element. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the wind related uncertainty subcategory element. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the wind related uncertainty subcategory element. Default is None. results (UncertaintyResults): Wind related uncertainty assessment subcategory element results.
